  <imageCaption>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color:#D81E5D;"&gt;FIGURE 10-10 &lt;/span&gt;The spinal cord, showing gray and white matter &lt;/strong&gt;(transverse view). &lt;strong&gt;Afferent neurons&lt;/strong&gt; bring impulses from a sensory receptor (such as the skin) into the spinal cord. &lt;strong&gt;Efferent neurons&lt;/strong&gt; carry impulses from the spinal cord to effector organs (such as skeletal muscle). The central canal is the space through which CSF travels.&lt;/p&gt;</imageCaption>
  <imageAlt/>
